description:
&lt;p&gt;We are ideally looking for someone to join our team within the Cellular Pathology Department who has experience working within an NHS laboratory and is looking to gain more hands-on experience and develop further within Cellular Pathology. Proven ability to undertake the basic techniques such as specimen reception, BMS &amp; Pathologist Cut-up assist, tissue processor maintenance. Experience of Microsoft Office, Word, Excel and confidence with IT programs is also very important.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A working knowledge of the APEX IT system would be a distinct advantage.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a busy modern department dealing with over 39000 cases per year, many are cancer and niche diagnostic cases requiring specialist work. For example we serve the Wessex Renal Transplant Unit based here at Portsmouth, we are a Beacon Site for Head &amp; Neck Cancer; we undertake large numbers of immunocytochemistry and are a key centre for Breast Sentinel Node PCR Assay procedures as well as other Molecular Pathology.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post offers a forward looking individual the opportunity to develop a wide range of skills in a competitive work environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A visit to the laboratory is encouraged – for more information please contact Charlotte Shepherd, Operational Manager Histopathology via charlotte.shepherd@porthosp.nhs.uk or call 02392 286000 ext 1775 or ext 5741.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing Date 16th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
